Is there a reason why this PR only addresses directional lights? 
We had problems with every kind of light affecting VoxelGI even when their bake mode was set to Disabled. So I checked out this PR and applied the changes you did to the 2 directional lights for loops in the `render_probes()` function to the 2 "generic lights" for loops as well and it worked!

So this:
```cpp
for (Instance *E : probe->lights) {
	Instance *instance = E;
	InstanceLightData *instance_light = (InstanceLightData *)instance->base_data;
	if (!instance->visible) {
		continue;
	}
```
gets the "disabled" check as well:
```cpp
for (Instance *E : probe->lights) {
	Instance *instance = E;
	InstanceLightData *instance_light = (InstanceLightData *)instance->base_data;
	RS::LightBakeMode bake_mode = RSG::light_storage->light_get_bake_mode(instance->base);
	if (!instance->visible || bake_mode == RS::LIGHT_BAKE_DISABLED) {
		continue;
	}
```
(And the same for the other "generic lights" for loop)

This is not a "do this!" comment, though. I don't know anything about these functions, I just tried out this PR as a shot in the dark for our very similar problem and it seems to also work for all kinds of lights 😄 Maybe someone who knows these functions can confirm whether this is the correct way to handle the "Disabled" bake mode?
I'll do some more testing and when I encounter problems I'll get back with another comment, but so far it just works as expected.

